docs.abstract: Facebook removed nearly 500 pages and accounts targeted at Eastern Europe and Central Asia. Some originated from an agency controlled by the Kremlin.
docs.snippet: Facebook removed nearly 500 pages and accounts targeted at Eastern Europe and Central Asia. Some originated from an agency controlled by the Kremlin.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Facebook identified two disinformation campaigns originating from Russia — including one tied to an agency controlled by the Kremlin — that were targeted at users in Europe and Central Asia. The company said on Thursday it had deleted nearly 500 pages and accounts that had posted the misleading messages.

headline.print_headline: Facebook Deletes Pages Of Russian Propaganda

docs.abstract: The reductions, which amount to 7 percent of Tesla’s work force, were necessary for the company to remain viable, Elon Musk wrote in an email to employees.
docs.snippet: The reductions, which amount to 7 percent of Tesla’s work force, were necessary for the company to remain viable, Elon Musk wrote in an email to employees.
docs.lead_paragraph: Tesla will reduce its full-time work force by 7 percent in an effort to lower the cost of producing its Model 3 sedan and make it a mass-market vehicle, Elon Musk, the electric-car maker’s chief executive, told employees on Friday.

headline.main: Tesla to Cut 3,000 Jobs in Bid to Sell Model 3 to Mass Market
headline.print_headline: Tesla to Cut 3,000 Jobs To Lower Model 3 Cost

docs.abstract: Occidental Petroleum announced a $38 billion bid for Anadarko Petroleum, challenging Chevron for control of the independent oil and gas company.

headline.main: Occidental Bids $38 Billion for Anadarko, Challenging Chevron
headline.print_headline: Occidental’s Bid for Anadarko Rattles Oil Business
